.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-auth-join-waitlist - Submit a waitlist entry to request access to BCDock


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock auth join-waitlist [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Join the BCDock waitlist with optional default environment configuration.

.PP
BCDock is currently in early access - we onboard users carefully so we can
get the experience right. After you submit, an admin reviews your entry and
emails you an invite code (typically within 48 hours). Once you have the
code, run:

.PP
bcdock auth signup --invite-code CODE --email you@example.com

.PP
Order of prompts (skip any with --flag or by pressing enter on optional ones):
  1. Default BC config - version, country, artifact type, region (all optional)
  2. What you'd like BCDock to help you with (optional)
  3. Your name (required)
  4. Your email (required)

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error
  4   rate-limited


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--artifact-type\fP=""
	Default artifact type: Sandbox or OnPrem

.PP
\fB--bc-version\fP=""
	Default BC version (optional)

.PP
\fB--country\fP=""
	Default BC country code (optional)

.PP
\fB--email\fP=""
	Email address (skips prompt)

.PP
\fB--expectations\fP=""
	What you'd like BCDock to help you with (optional)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for join-waitlist

.PP
\fB--multi-tenant\fP=""
	true|false - preferred multi-tenant default

.PP
\fB--name\fP=""
	Your name (skips prompt)

.PP
\fB--region\fP=""
	Preferred Azure region (optional)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock auth join-waitlist
  bcdock auth join-waitlist --name "Jane Smith" --email jane@example.com
  bcdock auth join-waitlist --name "Jane Smith" --email jane@example.com --bc-version 25.5 --country au --region australiaeast
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-auth(1)\fP
